########################
# Variables 
########################

Variable_Rules : 

  --  Identifiers can be combination of uppercase and lowercase letters, digits or an underscore(_). So my Variable, variable_1, variable_for_print all are valid python identifiers.

  --  An Identifier can not start with digit. So while variable1 is valid, 1variable is not valid.

  --  We can't use special symbols like !,#,@,%,$ etc in our Identifier.

  --  Identifier can be of any length.

