########################
# Types of Operators
########################


An operator is a symbol that performs a certain operation between operands.

   • Arithmetic Operators (* , - ,*, / ,%, **)
   
   • Relational / Comparison Operators (==,!= , > , <, ≥= , ≤= )        # it Answer only on True / False 
   
   • Assignment Operators  ( = , += , -= , *= , /= , %= , **= )
       
         Basic Exp =  a = 5
                      
                       
            so, New variable
                      a += 5           Ex -   + = 5 so 5+5 10 is answer
                      a += 10          Ex -   + = 5 so 5+5+1=  = 15 is answer

   • Logical Operators ( not, and , or )        - its work on Boolean Only

   if you want to print(True) its print True but you if say like this print(not True) its print False

Not operator - Work on only one value

    Ex : a = 5
         b = 5
       
         print(not (a == b))


And operator - Work on Two Value ( means two value must be true )

   Ex :  a = 5
         b = 10
         c = 5
         d = 5

        print((a == b) and (a ==c))       # If One is False it respond False
        print((a == b) and (a ==d))       # it check both variable must be true // If not it respond False



Or Operator - must be any one True then respond True / if both False then respond False

    Ex : a = 5
         b = 10

        print((a = b) or (a < b))      - Only One is True So it Respond True

Basic Intro
  
    -  Arithmetic Operation are for Mathematical operation like sum minus divide and all ( % - for 10/5 =)


########################
# Type Conversion
########################

type of conversion :  1) Automatical  -   Python do Automatical for use .
                      2) Casting      -   We have manually do it .

Automatic Conversion - Python do by himself

     a = 5        - integer
     b = 10.5     - float

     sum = a + b
     print(type(sum))       # sum type must be float

Casting

     a = "5"           # 5 is inside the  " " so its string not int
     b = 10.5 

     sum ( a + b)
     print(sum)          #  Error cant add string in flot
    
So change Type
    
      a = int("5")
      b = 10.5
    
     sum = a + b
     print(sum)   
     
